.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATETIME.MINUTE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDateTime.minute \- Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.minute
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]minute\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instances returns an integer from 0 to
59 representing the minute component of this time.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]minute\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]with()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] object with the desired new value.
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.minute\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using minute
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:34:56.123456789\(dq);
console.log(dt.minute); \f[I]// 34\f[R]
.EE
